<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="245" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,727,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Drew &amp; Hancock, D." authorityName="Drew &amp; Hancock, D." box="[603,1045,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Dacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis" subGenus="Mellesis">
<emphasis box="[603,630,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">D.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[646,677,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[692,801,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">siamensis</emphasis>
Drew &amp; Hancock, 
<emphasis box="[1017,1045,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">D.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1060,1091,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">M.</emphasis>
). 
<emphasis box="[1113,1233,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">tenebrosus</emphasis>
Drew &amp; Hancock and 
<taxonomicName authority="Drew &amp; Hancock" authorityName="Drew &amp; Hancock" authorityYear="1998" box="[198,644,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Dacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vijaysegarani" subGenus="Mellesis">
<emphasis box="[198,226,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">D.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[241,272,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[288,440,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">vijaysegarani</emphasis>
Drew &amp; Hancock
</taxonomicName>
but can be differentiated by the orange-brown patches on the abdomen and humped tergites II to IV. The Nauni specimen was collected at an altitude of 
<quantity box="[1078,1164,798,825]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" unit="m" value="1275.0">1275 m</quantity>
and is a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[151,212,835,861]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">India</collectingCountry>
; elsewhere it is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[592,676,835,861]" name="Bhutan" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
, generally above 
<quantity box="[872,957,835,861]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Romig, M. C. &amp; Dorji, C." box="[971,1166,835,861]" pageId="8" pageNumber="245" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref7286" refString="Drew, R. A. I., Romig, M. C. &amp; Dorji, C. (2007) Records of dacine fruit flies and new species of Dacus (Diptera: Tephritidae) in Bhutan. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 55 (1), 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2007">
Drew 
<emphasis box="[1042,1092,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="245">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
